The paper proposes a new LSTM neural network architecture for time series with exogenous variables, which is a common problem in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper also focuses on interpretability, which is a key concern in many applications of machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper uses statistical Granger causality test, which is a common method in signal processing and time series analysis, suggesting that cs.SI (Signal Processing) is also a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions experiments on real datasets, which suggests that cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is also a possible sub-category.
